Package RuleEngine.HierarchyProcessors

Class ConceptAttributeRelationalDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • RuleEngine.AbstractDefinition
        • RuleEngine.HierarchyProcessors.AttributeDefinition
          • RuleEngine.HierarchyProcessors.ConceptAttributeRelationalDefinition

  • public class ConceptAttributeRelationalDefinition
extends AttributeDefinition
    This class provides a processor for accessing realtional concept attributes. Since the attribute values of concept attributes are again concepts, one can apply further processors to the attribute values.
    The processor can do the following operations:
    - it can access the attribute values and put them into the query stream.
    - it can filter the attribute values and, thus, discard it from the stream.
    - it can call a sub-processor to further process the attribute values.

    The parameters for the processor are:
    - the concept is taken from the query stream (at conceptIndex)
    - the attribute is either predefined, or taken from the query stream (at attribute Index)
    - the output is either written to the query stream, or ignored. In this case the processor acts as filter.
    - filter and subProcessor must be defined explicitly.

    Note: If a sub-processor is defined, then the query array structure of the main processor and of the sub-processor must be identical. This can be achieved by adding a transformer to the sub-processor.
